crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a sophisticated loader/backdoor that demonstrates classic malware behaviors including process injection, anti-analysis via API hashing, and C2 communication. It manually resolves a large number of Windows Native APIs (NTDLL/Kernel32) by hash to evade static detection (sub_140007a90). Concrete malicious behaviors include process injection logic targeting 'notepad.exe' using NtCreateThreadEx/NtWriteVirtualMemory patterns (sub_140015e40, sub_140009bd0) and encrypted network communication using hardcoded browser User-Agents to blend with legitimate traffic (sub_14000c6d0). The sample also contains custom cryptographic routines (sub_1400011e0) used for decrypting internal payloads or C2 commands.
